strings:
<se_low>Yangus: Crikey!
Just lookin' at this tower does me 'ead in!
<se_low>Yangus: It's times like these when I'm really glad to 'ave you around, guv.
<se_def>Angelo: The cliffs looked high enough already from the ship, didn't they? And now this!
<se_def>Angelo: The top of the tower must reach the clouds.
<se_low>Yangus: Shame we couldn't get them Kran Spinels, eh.
<se_low>Yangus: Don't s'pose there's much point tellin' Dominico about it, though.
<se_def>Angelo: Jewels are like women.
<se_def>Angelo: The harder they are to get, the more satisfaction they bring in the end. Half the fun is in the chase, my friend. Let's go.
<se_low>Yangus: Here again? Feels like we're always trudgin' up towers recently.

<se_low>Yangus: Yer not<endash>
...Oh, we ain't goin' up there again, are we!?

<se_def>Angelo: Just looking at this tower makes me yawn.
There's only so much fun you can have on a see-saw.
<se_high>Jessica: Did you guys climb this tower while I was away?
<se_high>Jessica: I feel a little jealous that I missed out on the fun of exploring a new place together.
<se_low>Yangus: Here again? Feels like we're always trudgin' up towers recently.

<se_low>Yangus: Yer not<endash>
...Oh, we ain't goin' up there again, are we!?

<se_def>Angelo: Just looking at this tower makes me yawn.
There's only so much fun you can have on a see-saw.
<se_high>Jessica: I've been wondering. Did the Lord of Darkness know I would pick up the sceptre beforehand?

<se_high>Jessica: I hope I wasn't part of his master plan.
But even if I was, it would just be another reason to hate him!

<se_low>Yangus: We've seen a lot o' buildin's on our travels,
but this one takes the biscuit. I 'ate it!

<se_def>Angelo: Did you leave something behind?
If not, then we don't need to be here, do we?

<se_high>Red: Wot's this tower all about then, eh?
Wot's wiv all the see-saws?
You 'opin' to 'ave a little play time?
<se_low>Morrie: Ah ha! The person who made this place has the mind of the bambino, ay? Va bene! We use the saw-sees to get to the top of the tower!
<se_high>Red: Look, I'm all in favour of 'onin' our skills before we take on the Lord o' Darkness, but...pick yer places, eh?
<se_low>Morrie: The high places make my heart sing! And it seems the Lord of the Darkness likes them too, ay?
<se_low>Morrie: Si, maybe our towers are not tall enough to reach our nemesis. But with the power of the Godbird, we have him in our grass, ay?
